                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d765">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/4005: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Vice Consul at Viborg</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Imbrie</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-03-08T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 8, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your No. 3, March 2. Department has no adequate information regarding Russian
                    Whites referred to. This Government not in a position to offer any support or
                    assistance but wishes to be kept advised developments. You are to exercise
                    extreme caution not to encourage false hopes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
